From: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
Date: Fri, 5 Jun 2015 09:42:09 +0200
Subject: firmware: iBFT firmware is also supported on EFI machines with ACPI
References: bsc#932047
Patch-Mainline: n/a

The iBFT firmware tables can also be specified via ACPI tables
when using EFI firmware.

Signed-off-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/firmware/Kconfig | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/firmware/Kconfig b/drivers/firmware/Kconfig
index 25e88a5..cb39e6a 100644
--- a/drivers/firmware/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/firmware/Kconfig
@@ -128,7 +128,7 @@ config DMI_SYSFS
 
 config ISCSI_IBFT_FIND
 	bool "iSCSI Boot Firmware Table Attributes"
-	depends on X86
+	depends on X86 || (EFI && ACPI)
 	default n
 	help
 	  This option enables the kernel to find the region of memory
